$101_{10}$ can be written in terms of powers of 2 as $101 = 64 + 32 + 4 + 1 = 2^6 + 2^5 + 2^2 + 2^0$, so its binary representation is $\boxed{1100101_2}$.

***

$16_{10}$ is already a power of 2 ($2^4$), so its binary representation will have 1 bit set: $\boxed{10000_2}$.&#x20;

